Reference-contexts: Our approach extends previous work generalizing the Kolmogorov-Smirnov (K-S) and Kuiper goodness-of-fit tests, suggesting additional, powerful tests that can be tailored to the known symmetries of a situation <ref> (Feltz and Goldin, 1992) </ref>. The result is also a conceptual unification of many seemingly disparate or ad hoc tests discussed in the literature. Finally, we explore the first few of the natural series of distribution-free tests following from our analysis, using numerical simulation. <p> Ahmad (1993) modified Watson's statistic (1.4), to obtain asymptotically normal null distributions. Our earlier work <ref> (Feltz and Goldin, 1992) </ref> included a series of consistent generalizations D (k) n of the K-S test on R 1 , which we called k-point tests (k = 1; 2; 3; : : :). - 4 - The case k = 1 is the K-S test (1.1), and the case k
